<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link><description>World News Today: Read the latest world news headlines, Current International breaking news world wide. In depth analysis and top news headlines world wide.</description><language>en-gb</language><lastBuildDate>2026-07-16T00:41:17+05:30</lastBuildDate><atom:link type="application/rss+xml" rel="self" href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/rssfeeds/296589292.cms"/><copyright>Copyright:(C) Thu, 16 Jul 2026 00:41:17 IST Bennett Coleman &amp; Co. Ltd, http://in.indiatimes.com/policyterms/1554651.cms</copyright><docs>http://syndication.indiatimes.com/</docs><image><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><url>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/507610.cms</url><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link></image><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Cyrus the Great: 'All men have their frailties; and whoever looks for a friend...']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132423461.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Cyrus the Great, an ancient king, cautioned against the pursuit of flawless friendships. He recognized that accepting human imperfections contributed to the foundation of a strong empire. In today's world, technology magnifies our quest for perfect relationships, often resulting in loneliness. This unrealistic pursuit stifles meaningful connections. By embracing imperfections, we can nurture deeper and more resilient bonds with one another.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/quote-of-the-day-by-cyrus-the-great-all-men-have-their-frailties-and-whoever-looks-for-a-friend-without-imperfections-will-never-find-what-he-seeks-and-how-the-search-for-perfection-is-a-rejection-of-humanity-itself/articleshow/132423461.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/quote-of-the-day-by-cyrus-the-great-all-men-have-their-frailties-and-whoever-looks-for-a-friend-without-imperfections-will-never-find-what-he-seeks-and-how-the-search-for-perfection-is-a-rejection-of-humanity-itself/articleshow/132423461.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-16T00:37:43+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132424252,imgsize-309922.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[This billionaire lived six months a year on his 233-foot superyacht to avoid paying land taxes]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132420665.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Innovative Microsoft engineer Charles Simonyi cleverly leveraged a bespoke superyacht to sidestep local taxation and stringent construction regulations. This mobile abode enabled him to traverse the globe while circumventing substantial property tax liabilities. His forward-thinking strategy predates ongoing discussions surrounding wealth taxation in high-levy regions. A trailblazer in digital technology and space tourism, he eventually acquired an even grander superyacht to enhance his aquatic adventures.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/this-tech-billionaire-lived-six-months-a-year-on-his-233-foot-superyacht-to-avoid-paying-property-taxes-on-land-in-california-and-new-york/articleshow/132420665.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/this-tech-billionaire-lived-six-months-a-year-on-his-233-foot-superyacht-to-avoid-paying-property-taxes-on-land-in-california-and-new-york/articleshow/132420665.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-16T00:01:59+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132422887,imgsize-339866.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Right to die: French Parliament approves assisted dying bill after years of debate]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132422380.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/right-to-die-french-parliament-approves-assisted-dying-bill-after-years-of-debate/articleshow/132422380.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/right-to-die-french-parliament-approves-assisted-dying-bill-after-years-of-debate/articleshow/132422380.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-15T23:21:02+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132422416,imgsize-316250.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Jones Act waiver extension on the table as Iran tensions threaten US fuel prices - report]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132421196.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/jones-act-waiver-extension-on-the-table-as-iran-tensions-threaten-us-fuel-prices-report/articleshow/132421196.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/jones-act-waiver-extension-on-the-table-as-iran-tensions-threaten-us-fuel-prices-report/articleshow/132421196.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-15T22:45:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132421536,imgsize-74484.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Who is Kenichi Takano? Japanese man sentenced to 16 years for killing streamer Airi Sato during Tokyo livestream]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132421173.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Kenichi Takano has been sentenced to 16 years in prison for killing 22-year-old streamer Airi Sato during her livestream in Tokyo. The court found that he intentionally carried out the attack despite a financial dispute between them. The case shocked people around the world because thousands of viewers were watching Sato’s livestream when the attack happened, bringing renewed attention to creator safety.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/who-is-kenichi-takano-japanese-man-sentenced-to-16-years-for-killing-streamer-airi-sato-during-tokyo-livestream/articleshow/132421173.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/who-is-kenichi-takano-japanese-man-sentenced-to-16-years-for-killing-streamer-airi-sato-during-tokyo-livestream/articleshow/132421173.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-15T22:31:40+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132421119,imgsize-70693.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[A scientist slipped into a pool beneath a US military base and found a 'demon cavefish']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132419368.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a remarkable finding, a scientist has uncovered a new species of eyeless fish in Bobcat Cave, aptly named the demon cavefish after a character from a popular TV series. This fascinating creature has evolved to thrive in complete darkness, displaying no eyes or pigmentation. Intriguingly, it cohabits with another sightless predator, showcasing the resilience of unique wildlife beneath humanity's constructed environments.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-scientist-slipped-into-a-pool-beneath-a-us-military-base-and-found-a-fish-later-named-demon-cavefish-after-the-demogorgon-from-stranger-things/articleshow/132419368.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-scientist-slipped-into-a-pool-beneath-a-us-military-base-and-found-a-fish-later-named-demon-cavefish-after-the-demogorgon-from-stranger-things/articleshow/132419368.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-15T22:04:49+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132420101,imgsize-125068.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[New highway hurt his town. At 98, he helped revive America's famous Route 66]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132408578.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/a-new-highway-nearly-killed-his-town-this-98-year-old-angel-of-route-66-helped-bring-americas-most-famous-highway-back-to-life/articleshow/132408578.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/a-new-highway-nearly-killed-his-town-this-98-year-old-angel-of-route-66-helped-bring-americas-most-famous-highway-back-to-life/articleshow/132408578.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-15T12:29:17+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132408766,imgsize-194802.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[120-year-old North Atlantic right whale skeleton returns to Hull Museum after 6 years]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132409878.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A nearly 120-year-old whale skeleton has returned to Hull Maritime Museum after extensive conservation work. Visitors can now crawl through a tunnel inside the rib cage, offering a new perspective. The skeleton, which is 117 years old, was originally found off the coast of New York. This critically endangered species, with fewer than 400 remaining, serves as an important historical reminder.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-120-year-old-north-atlantic-right-whale-skeleton-left-hull-museum-for-conservation-6-years-ago-now-it-has-returned-as-the-centrepiece-of-a-new-gallery/articleshow/132409878.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-120-year-old-north-atlantic-right-whale-skeleton-left-hull-museum-for-conservation-6-years-ago-now-it-has-returned-as-the-centrepiece-of-a-new-gallery/articleshow/132409878.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-15T16:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132409878,imgsize-132032.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Neanderthals nearly disappeared 75,000 years ago, but one small group in France repopulated Europe]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132414659.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/neanderthals-nearly-disappeared-75000-years-ago-but-one-small-group-in-france-repopulated-europe/articleshow/132414659.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/res